The paper deals with image landmark recognition, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an ensemble network that uses both supervised feature-based classification algorithms and Graph-Based Visual Saliency (GBVS) network, which involves machine learning techniques. This makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also deals with image processing and analysis, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves evaluation of the proposed model, which can be considered as a form of information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category.
